# .NET build artifacts — regenerated by `dotnet build`/`dotnet restore`.
# Machine-specific, large, never useful in source control.
**/bin/
**/obj/

# Per-user IDE state (Rider/VS):
#   *.user         — per-user project settings (Debug profile, etc.)
#   *.suo          — VS solution user options (binary)
*.user
*.suo

# Local-only env file. The committed `.env.local.example` documents the
# variable layout; copy it to `.env.local` for actual credentials. The
# repo-root .gitignore already excludes `.env.local`, this entry is here
# for visibility next to the code.
.env.local

# Properties/launchSettings.json holds VS F5 environment variables.
# Operators routinely put real DB credentials directly in here (it's
# the only ergonomic path for VS-based dev). We gitignore it so those
# creds never reach the repository; new contributors get the same
# variable layout from `.env.local.example` and create their own
# launchSettings.json locally.
src/Insight.Identity.Api/Properties/launchSettings.json
